Package: elfgen
Title: Ecological Limit Function Model Generation and Analysis Toolkit
Version: 2.3.3
Authors@R: person(given = "Joseph", family = "Kleiner", role = c("aut",
        "cre"), email = "joseph.d.kleiner@gmail.com", comment = c(ORCID
        = "0000-0003-4837-7678") )
Maintainer: Joseph Kleiner <joseph.d.kleiner@gmail.com>
Description: A toolset for generating Ecological Limit Function (ELF)
        models and evaluating potential species loss resulting from
        flow change, based on the 'elfgen' framework. ELFs describe the
        relation between aquatic species richness (fish or benthic
        macroinvertebrates) and stream size characteristics (streamflow
        or drainage area). Journal publications are available outlining
        framework methodology (Kleiner et al. (2020)
        <doi:10.1111/1752-1688.12876>) and application (Rapp et al.
        (2020) <doi:10.1111/1752-1688.12877>).
Imports: utils, stringr, quantreg, stats, ggplot2, testit, scales,
        sqldf, curl, sbtools, nhdplusTools
